1 H. Prior to conviction, parties in criminal cases shall not be
2 required to pay, advance, or post security for the issuance or
3 service of process to obtain compulsory attendance of witnesses.
4 I. The amounts to be assessed as court costs upon filing of a
5 case shall be those amounts above-stated in paragraph 3 or 4 of
6 subsection A and subsections B, C, D and E of this section.
7 J. The fees collected pursuant to this section shall be
8 deposited into the court fund, except the following:
9 1. A court clerk issuing a misdemeanor warrant is entitled to
10 ten percent (10%) of the sheriff’s service fee, provided for in
11 paragraph 9 13 of subsection A of this section, collected on a
12 warrant referred to the contractor for the misdemeanor warrant
13 notification program governed by Sections 514.4 and 514.5 of Title
14 19 of the Oklahoma Statutes. This ten-percent sum shall be
15 deposited into the issuing Court Clerk’s Revolving Fund, created
16 pursuant to Section 220 of Title 19 of the Oklahoma Statutes, of the
17 court clerk issuing the warrant with the balance of the sheriff’s
18 service fee to be deposited into the Sheriff’s Service Fee Account,
19 created pursuant to the provisions of Section 514.1 of Title 19 of
20 the Oklahoma Statutes, of the sheriff in the county in which service
21 is made or attempted. Otherwise, the sheriff’s service fee, when
22 collected, shall be deposited in its entirety into the Sheriff’s
23 Service Fee Account of the sheriff in the county in which service is
24 made or attempted;
